\begin_layout Chapter
CPOE and Drug Calculations
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The programming of drug calculations procedure is hard.
 This might be the author's prespective from her experience maintaining
 CPOE, nevertheless it has many details and formulas to apply, depending
 on the situation, fields become editable or calculated, while reserving
 the edited values.
 The difficulty derived from the amount of information, and also from the
 large codebase which is reflected it, by recurring code of calculations.
 OOP should be a good idea to seperate the information and reduce the code
 duplication.
 For the simplicity, we will go into details, by a minimalistic drug-calculation
 user interface.
 
\end_layout

