\begin_layout Standard
There are two use cases (for this scope).
 First, a clinician set values for the dose, duration and then to the volume.
 after setting value to the duration, drug's value is calculated by multiplying
 dose and duration's values.
 Then, after setting value to the volume, the concentration's value is calculati
ng by deviding the calculated value of drug with the new value of the volume.
 Additionaly after settings value the the volume, the rate's value is calculated
 by the volume's value devided by the duration's value.
 The second use-case, a clinician set values for drug, dose and then to
 the rate.
 After setting values to the drug and dose, the duration' value is calculated
 by deviding drug with dose.
 Then, after setting the rate, the volume's value is calculated by multiplying
 rates value with the duration value.
 The volume new value follows also calculating the concentration's value
 as in the first use-case.
\end_layout

